.\" SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT
.Dd April 5, 2026
.Dt PUNCHCARD 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm punchcard
.Nd generates SVG files for use in diecutting machines, for punchcards for 12 or 24 stitch punch card knitting machines
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Fl o Ar output_path
.Op Fl d Ar recreate_directories
.Op Cm --stitches Ar 12|24
.Op Cm --layout Ar auto|motif|repeat
.Op Cm --repeat-height Ar n
.Op Cm --threshold Ar 0-255
.Op Cm --invert
.Op Cm --hole-ratio Ar 0-1
.Op Cm --cell-size Ar n
.Op Cm --margin Ar n
.Ar input ...
.Op Ar stitches
.Op Ar layout
.Op Ar repeat_height
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
converts 1:1 image motifs (1 pixel = 1 stitch) into punch cards in cut-ready SVG files for use with electronic die cutters.
It is designed for 12-stitch and 24-stitch punch card knitting machines.
.Pp
One or more input files may be provided.
When positional shorthand is used, trailing values apply to all listed input files.
.Pp
Layout modes follow the same behavior described in the README and QuickStart guides:
.Dq motif
centers a motif,
.Dq repeat
tiles across card width, and
.Dq auto
chooses between them from width compatibility.
.Pp
Positional arguments are interpreted as:
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Ar input
One or more input image paths. Supported types: PNG and PCX.
.It Ar stitches
Card width in stitches. Allowed values: 12 or 24. Default: 24.
.It Ar layout
Card composition mode: auto, motif, repeat. Default: auto.
.It Ar repeat_height
Vertical repeat count. Must be >= 1. Default: 1.
.El
.Sh OPTIONS
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Fl o Ar output_path
Write generated file(s) into this directory.
.It Fl d Ar recreate_directories
Recreate input folder structure under destination root.
.It Cm --stitches Ar 12|24
Card width in stitches. Default is 24.
.It Cm --layout Ar auto|motif|repeat
Card layout mode. Default is auto.
.It Cm --repeat-height Ar n
Vertical repeat count. Must be >= 1. Default is 1.
.It Cm --threshold Ar 0-255
Pixels below threshold are treated as punch holes.
Default is 255.
.It Cm --invert
Invert punch mapping (bright becomes punch).
.It Cm --hole-ratio Ar 0-1
Relative punch-hole diameter for SVG output.
Default is 0.55.
.It Cm --cell-size Ar n
Cell size for simple SVG grid rendering.
Default is 10.
.It Cm --margin Ar n
Outer margin for simple SVG grid rendering.
Default is 12.
.El
.Sh EXAMPLES
Generate a 24-stitch punch chard with a centered motif and 6 vertical repeats:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
punchcard design.png 24 motif 6
.Ed
.Pp
Generate a 12-stitch punch card with a pattern that repeats across the width of the card and 4 vertical repeats:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
punchcard tile.png 12 repeat 4
.Ed
.Pp
Use defaults (24 stitch punch chard, auto layout, 1 vertical repeat):
.Bd -literal -offset indent
punchcard design.pcx
.Ed
.Pp
Batch process PCX/PNG files from stdin:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
find . -name "*.pcx" | punchcard 24 repeat 3
.Ed
.Pp
Batch process with shell glob expansion:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
punchcard *.pcx 24 motif 2 -d /path/to/output/dir
.Ed
.Sh EXIT STATUS
.Ex -std
.Sh DIAGNOSTICS
Common failures include unsupported input extension, invalid repeat height,
and repeat layout width mismatch.
.Pp
Typical messages include:
.Bl -bullet
.It
.Dq Unsupported file format
.It
.Dq Motif width is wider than card width
.It
.Dq Repeat source width must evenly divide card width
.El
.Sh FILES
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Pa *.punch.svg
Generated SVG punchcard output.
.El
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr python3 1
.Sh AUTHORS
.An Kevin Duncan
